Description. MALE. Body length 4.5−5 mm . Shape. Head transverse ( 0.73−0.80 ), wider than mesosoma. Antenna attaining posterior end of scutum; pedicel as long as wide, shorter than F 1 ; F 1 conical, as long as wide apically, equaling F 3 ; F 2 short, transverse, longer than half F 1 ; F 3 slightly wider than long; other flagellomeres as long as wide or slightly longer. Labral plate rounded, twice as wide as long, with transverse depression (
Fig. 65
). Facial fovea deep, narrow, apically not enlarged, as wide as distance to eye. Genal area narrower than eye ( 0.6−0.7 ; specimens from Mongolia − 0.85 ), wide on 2 / 3 of length. Middle basitarsus 5 times, hind basitarsus 4.5–5 times as long as wide, parallel-sided. Middle and hind TM 2 and TM 3 conical, elongate, TM 4 cordate, as long as wide. Metasomal terga with marginal zone depressed, medially enlarged, on T 1 ca 1 / 3 , on other terga ca 1 / 2 discal length. Pregenital Sterna & Genitalia (
Figs 64, 66− 72
). S 2 −S 5 shiny, deeply tessellate, on disc laterally and preapically with sparse, tiny hair pores a few diameters apart (ca 5 μm /> 4 ). S 3 −S 5 posterior margins slightly incurved; S 4 and S 5 with marginal zone depressed stronger than on S 2 and S 3 , with short, dense, yellowish hair fringe, longer on S 5 . S 2 −S 4 preapically slightly swelled. S 6 posterior margin medially widely arcuate and bent ventrally at 45 °, with dense hair fringe (lateral view); in ventral view, lateral margins of the lamella look like widely spaced, short, pointed teeth; posterior shoulders of the sternum narrowly rounded, pooled backwards. S 7 apically with 2 teeth narrowly separated to their bases (ventral view), directed ventro-posteriorly at 30 °, straight, latero-laterally flattened, about 3 times as long as wide basally (lateral view); posterior shoulders narrowly rounded (ca 90 °), directed posteriorly, with posterior margin long, horizontal and incurved. S 8 neck short, wide, with lateral flaps transverse, less than half length of neck; apical plate as long as wide, without keel, with basal hill obtusely angled. Gonocoxite with shallow dorso-apical depression. Gonostylus narrow, parallel-sided, apically rounded, at halflength bowed inside. Penis valve pale, narrow, apically shortly bulging and bent inside, dorsally with a few erect hairs. Sculpture. Shiny, finely sculptured. Paraocular area on upper part and vertex shagreened, with pits 1−2 diameters apart to confluent ( 10−15 µm / 0.5−2 ); paraocular area below smooth, with deep pits 1−2 diameters apart ( 15−25 µm / 1−2 ). Frons with fine, transversal, shallow wrinkles and punctures, laterally tessellate and impunctate. Genal area shiny, slightly tessellate or smooth, with pits less than a diameter apart to confluent ( 15−25 µm / 0.5−2 ). Supraclypeal area shiny, finely shagreened, with small pits about a few diameters apart; subantennal areas glossy, smooth or delicately tessellate. Clypeus shiny, smooth, with shallow pits about 2 diameters apart ( 1−4 ). Scutum and scutellum shiny, delicately tessellate, medially smoother, with dense, irregularly spaced, deep, large pits ( 10−20 µm / 0.5−2 ) and shallow punctures; on periphery pits smaller and denser to confluent. Tegula anteriorly punctured confluently, posteriorly impunctate. Scutellum on disc glossy, with large pits widely separated ( 10−20 µm / up to 5−6 ); on periphery shagreened. Metanotum shagreened, with shallow, small, round pits merged. Mesepisternum matt, shagreened, with large, shallow pits 1−3 diameters apart ( 15−25 µm / 1−3 ). Propodeum shagreened; horizontal part of propodeal triangle rugose, often with a median ray, vertical part tessellated. Metasomal terga shiny, tessellate, with punctures a few diameters apart and marginal zone delicately tessellate, impunctate; T 1 −T 3 medially glossy; T 1 basally with punctures denser than on disc; disc and marginal zone smoother than on following terga. Coloration. Wing brown or yellowish-brown, veins and tegulae pale or dark brown. Antenna beneath yellow to brown. Clypeus yellow, with apical and lateral margins narrowly brown. Fore tibiae anteriorly, all knees, tarsi and spurs yellow. Hind basitarsi and sometimes other tarsal segments darkened. Vestiture. Metasomal terga on disc with dense, recumbent, thin, short, white hairs laterally and on apical terga long; T 6 and T 7 with long hair fimbria grayish.
